I"e<p>A few days ago, Microsoft announced the preview of direct-upload to Azure Managed Disks. So, there are two ways you could move a VHD to the Azure cloud as a managed disk:</p>
<ol>
  <li>Upload the VHD in a storage account, and then convert it into a managed disk.</li>
  <li>Create and attach empty managed disk to a VM, and then do the copy.</li>
</ol>
